e person behind the camera. In the context of digital imagery, however, these aesthetic strategies had the opposite effect, heightening the sense of realism by calling on tropes suggesting the authenticity to which viewers were accustomed. ILM’s style, on display in the most successful films of the 1980s and beyond, was so convincing that other studios were forced to follow suit, and today, ILM is a victim of its own success, having fostered a cinematic monoculture in which it is but one player among many.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCinematographyxSpecial effectsxHistory. 0aComputer animationxHistory. 0aDigital cinematographyxHistory. 0aMotion picture industryxHistory. 0aMotion picturesxAestheticsxHistory. 0aRealism in motion picturesxHistory. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / General.2bisacsh  aspecial effects, special effects in filmmaking, film production, cinematography, Star Wars franchise, Star Wars, film technology, blockbusters, Visual Effects.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2022z9783110992809oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2022 Englishz978311099281608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Texas Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z97831107665160 cprintz978147732530840uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/32530840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781477325315423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781477325315/original  a978-3-11-076651-6  University of Texas Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099281-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture